<TEXT>
rumeal robinson made two free throws with three 
seconds left in overtime to give michigan its first national 
championship in collegiate basketball with an 8079 victory over 
seton hall monday night 
the championship game in the national collegiate athletic 
association tournament was the fifth to go into overtime and the 
first since loyola ill beat cincinnati 6058 in 1963 
glen rice carried the wolverines to the title with 31 points in 
the final giving him an ncaa tournament record 184 breaking the 
24yearold mark of 177 set by bill bradley of princeton 
michigans coach steve fisher took over the team just two days 
before the ncaa tournament began and coached them through six 
victories to the title 
