<TEXT>
chronology of events in haiti 
oct 22 1957 francois papa doc duvalier becomes president 
in disputed election and in 1964 proclaims himself president for 
life 
april 21 1971 duvalier dies and 19yearold jeanclaude 
baby doc duvalier becomes president 
feb 7 1986 duvalier flees to exile in france after a month 
of antigovernment unrest leaves more than 50 people dead a 
threeman junta led by duvaliers army chief of staff lt gen 
henri namphy takes power 
march 29 1987 voters overwhelmingly approve a new 
constitution putting elections for a president and national 
assembly in the hands of a civilian election commission 
nov 29 election day thugs kill at least 34 voters and 
confiscate ballots the election is called off three hours after it 
begins namphy and junta dissolve election commission the united 
states suspends 70 million in aid in protest 
jan 17 1988 leslie manigat a 57yearold university 
professor is elected president in the newly scheduled elections 
few haitians vote and most opposition leaders refuse to 
participate 
june 19 troops storm the national palace deposing manigat and 
replacing him with namphy namphy abolishes the national assembly a 
day later 
sept 17 namphy is ousted in a coup led by noncommissioned 
officers and exiled in the neighboring dominican republic 
sept 18 lt gen prosper avril chief of the presidential 
guard and a former duvalier adviser declares himself president 
march 13 1989 avril partially restores the suspended 1987 
constitution 
march 28 four highranking army officers are reportedly 
accused of drug trafficking and discharged the action comes one 
day after a us official ties resumption of us aid to progress 
in stopping the drug trade 
april 2 gunfire breaks out at the presidential palace the 
government later says it has foiled a coup attempt by rebel 
officers the us embassy says loyal soldiers rescued avril as he 
was being driven away to be deported 
april 3 avril goes on national television to announce that the 
coup has ended unsuccessfully and says powerhungry soldiers were 
behind it 
april 4 government placates rebel soldiers by releasing and 
deporting three army officers who led the coup attempt against 
avril rebel soldiers accept new commander and insurgency seems 
over 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

