ceasefire monitoring forces in northern namibia 
the united nations authorized 4650 troops for the namibia 
operation but only about 1000 have arrived and no more than 300 
are in northern namibia the un forces made no effort to 
intervene in the fighting and say it is not part of their mandate 
perez de cuellar said monday in new york the fighting did not 
mean un peacekeeping efforts had broken down 
