<TEXT>
the first battles following any major 
change in the us supreme courts 1973 ruling legalizing abortion 
probably would erupt in louisiana and 14 other states that still 
have antiabortion laws on the books 
the laws now are unenforceable because of the roe vs wade 
decision but there is debate over whether they could take effect 
if the high court ever overturned the 1973 ruling the issue would 
head immediately for the courts 
louisianas law says that if the high court ever reverses the 
1973 decision the states antiabortion rules go back into force 
idaho and illinois have similar laws 
our law is broad and general and says the state can regulate 
abortions totally within limits of the us supreme court 
decisions said jo anne lavert a staff attorney for attorney 
general william guste 
however democratic state rep woody jenkins who has written 
most of louisianas antiabortion laws since 1973 said he doubted 
the laws could take effect again and predicted a new law would have 
to be passed 
daniel stier an assistant attorney general in wisconsin which 
has an antiabortion law on the books from before the 1973 ruling 
said he was not sure what would happen 
until we get a decision its so speculative it would be a 
waste of time to guess what the effect would be on wisconsin law 
he said there are an infinite number of possibilities of what 
might happen to the laws on our books 
stier said he would advise district attorneys not to begin 
prosecuting women for violating state law if the supreme court 
reversed roe vs wade 
walter turner an assistant state attorney general in alabama 
said his office could not speak specifically about the states 1852 
antiabortion law unless the supreme court overturned roe vs wade 
but he said there had been previous cases in which old state laws 
went back into effect after the supreme court reversed itself 
the other states with antiabortion laws predating roe vs wade 
are arkansas arizona connectituct delaware michigan 
mississippi new hampshire oklahoma south dakota and west 
virginia an attempt to repeal new hampshires law has passed the 
