mystic pizza virgin vision vhsbeta 8995 rated r 
 
the three young women who serve up mystic pizza at a small 
restaurant in the coastal connecticut town of mystic are real 
charmers 
one annabeth gish is naive and serious and headed to yale 
university her sister julia roberts is sexy and independent and 
terrified she has nothing to look forward to and their feisty 
friend lili taylor is determined to break out of her 
workingclass mold 
mystic pizza is a slice of their lives spiced with romance 
that thrills amuses and sometimes disappoints the women but the 
best scenes are in the pizza parlor presided over by a cook 
conchata ferrell who refuses to divulge the secret of her sauce 
their town populated by workingclass people who make a living 
from the fishing industry and by the connecticut upper class is 
beautifully photographed 
the three women give excellent performances vincent phillip 
donofrio is very good as the young man who wants to marry taylor 
but the plot is too predictable and the feel a little too sappy 
still mystic pizza would make a fine accompaniment to a 
neighborhood pie with all the works and an evening at home 
by mary macvean associated press writer 
</TEXT>
