lockheed corp announced the creation 
of a 500 million employee stock ownership plan today one day 
after an investor group said it held a 53 percent stake in the 
aerospace company 
lockheed said it would issue 105 million new shares for its 
employee stock ownership plan known as an esop then buy back the 
same number of shares on the open market the buyback was intended 
to offset the dilutive effects of the plan on the companys 
oustanding stock lockheed said 
many companies have used esops as defensive moves against 
hostile takeover attempts last month polaroid corp defeated an 
unwanted bid from shamrock holdings inc with an esop as part of 
its defensive strategy 
we dont deny it has defensive characteristics but that was 
not the primary purpose for the esop lockheed spokesman bob 
slayman said today the primary purpose is to create employee 
incentive tied to shareholder growth and value 
on monday dallas investor harold c simmons disclosed that his 
group valhi inc has a 53 percent stake in lockheed but slayman 
said today that the esop had been under consideration here for 
some time 
simmons said his groups stake in lockheed bodes no takeover 
attempt of the aerospace giant a company he said is running just 
fine as it is 
the company has taken defensive steps against simmons in the 
past when valhi said last december it wanted to increase its 
holdings to more than 15 million lockheed said it was 
implementing a poison pill shareholder rights plan 
the plan would allow current shareholders to buy newly issued 
stock at a discount if an outsider buys 20 percent or more of the 
common stock the effect would be to make it much more expensive 
for someone to take over the company 
in december valhi owned 063 percent of lockheeds 595 million 
outstanding shares 
in midday trading on the new york stock exchange today lockheed 
fell 875 cents to 4887 a share after a delayed opening the 
stock rose 3 a share on monday 
lockheed also announced steps today to help reduce its costs 
the company said it would phase out its information systems 
group and sell the groups four units no asking price was given 
lockheed also said it would sell real estate in burbank calif 
made available by the ongoing relocation of its aeronautical 
systems division to sites in california and georgia the company 
said its was accelerating the relocation to take advantage of what 
it called more efficient facilities 
these steps and the esop will enhance our competitiveness in a 
rapidly changing environment where premiums are placed on 
innovation efficientcy quality and focused management lockheed 
chairman daniel m tellup said 
simmons said in a telephone interview monday he did not intend 
to try to take over the aerospace giant which produces the secret 
f117a stealth fighter and is home to the famed skunk works 
the advanced development project area at lockheeds burbank plant 
where such innovations as the p80 the nations first fighter jet 
and the highflying u2 and sr71 spy planes were developed 
simmons said he might sell some of his stock if it rises another 
3 he said he had not considered how many shares of lockheed he 
might buy 
we view lockheed as a wellmanaged company simmons said in 
a friday letter to lockheed management a copy of which he released 
monday we have no plans or desire to disrupt management we 
expect to be a constructive longterm shareholder 
simmons said he is investing in lockheed because he believes its 
stock was undervalued late last year due to anticipated cuts in the 
federal defense budget lockheed share prices were at 39 and 
averaged into the low 40s when he began acquiring them he said 
in february lockheed reported profit from continuing operations 
rose 35 percent in 1988 but profit rose 48 percent if proceeds of 
the sale of its dialog computerized information services were 
included 
lockheed said it earned 624 million or 1037 a share in 
1988 up from 421 million or 641 a share the previous year 
that profit was boosted 182 by the sale of dialog 
lockheed defense projects include the radarevading stealth 
fighter the trident 11 nuclear missile the c5b transport plane 
and work on military communications satellites and the strategic 
defense initiative or star wars the company is also a 
subcontractor for design work on nasas space station project 
