1985 will expire next year 
some want the 1985 law extended a year or two so that any gatt 
settlement can be considered as new legislation is drafted 
i dont think we should write a farm bill based on what we 
hope will happen in the gatt talks kleckner told a news 
conference 
the united states and the 12nation eec are hung up mainly on 
longterm strategy and by what us negotiators insist are 
distortions caused by certain subsidies and restrictive policies 
but eec officials claim there has been progress in overhauling 
the communitys policies and that the united states should 
compromise on some of its goals which at one time called for the 
