oil flow through the transalaska pipeline 
was increased again tuesday and will return to its normal daily 
level of 21 million barrels wednesday alyeska pipeline service 
co said 
flow through the pipeline had been cut by 60 percent because of 
restrictions on tanker travel through valdez harbor after the exxon 
valdez accident 
alyeska spokeswoman beverly michaels said tankers may now handle 
the normal load even though some coast guard travel restrictions 
are still in effect 
inventory is very low so we still have storage in valdez to 
handle it ms michaels said and we are able to bring in 
enough tankers 
the coast guard on monday restricted traffic to daytime hours 
only and required a twotug escort for tankers in addition only 
one tanker at a time is allowed to pass through the area 
valdez is the only port from which north slope oil is shipped 
the reductions have caused west coast refinery shortages and higher 
oil prices 
the coast guard said valdez averages three tankers a day and 
were not too far away from that 
