cathay pacific airways announced tuesday that it 
has placed a firm order with airbus industrie for 10 a330300 
aircraft and has taken options on another 10 of the widebody 
planes 
the firm order is worth about 11 billion and if all the 
options are exercised the order would total about 22 billion 
the hong kong airline said 
the first of the planes will be delivered in january 1995 with 
delivery scheduled to be completed in 1997 
the purchase is the largest single airbus order by a far eastern 
airline cathay pacific said airbus industrie is a european 
aircraftmaking consortium sponsored by the governments of britain 
france west germany and spain 
this huge investment demonstrates cathay pacifics commitment 
to hong kong and our confidence in the territory up to and beyond 
